'''''Chisholm Trail''''' is a [[video game]] released in July 1982 by [[Texas Instruments]] for its [[TI-99/4A]] home computer.<ref name= "book" /> It was written by John C. Plaster, who previously wrote ''[[Tombstone City: 21st Century]]'' for the TI-99/4A.

==Gameplay==
Players take the role of a [[cattle drive]]r on the [[Chisholm Trail]], bringing their cattle to set destinations while defending them against [[Cattle raiding|cattle rustlers]] and wranglers. The game has nine levels.<ref name=book/> You can choose any of the levels from the start menu and the level selected determines how long you have been on the trail, how many steers you have, how many shots you have, and how many wranglers and rustlers must be eliminated. 
